right now.

14:13.936 --> 14:15.893
Yeah, real stupid.

14:16.189 --> 14:19.022
Listen, I've got something
serious to tell both of you.

14:19.317 --> 14:23.606
What?
Please let me do it. Please.

14:23.905 --> 14:27.398
No, no, no.

14:27.700 --> 14:29.316
Goodbye, Dave.

14:29.619 --> 14:31.030
[SOBS]

14:33.581 --> 14:34.787
Oh, my God.

14:35.083 --> 14:36.949
So Grant dumped you
on Valentine's Day?

14:37.251 --> 14:39.618
What did you do?
Nothing. Literally nothing.

14:39.921 --> 14:43.915
Happy Valentine's Day.

14:44.217 --> 14:44.877
Were we supposed
to hang out today?

14:45.927 --> 14:50.592
| double booked,
you and this pizza.

14:50.890 --> 14:52.801
So you took Grant for granted?

14:53.101 --> 14:54.262
Oh, God.

14:54.560 --> 14:56.142
That made me sad
when you said that.

14:56.437 --> 14:57.927
Well, it's the truth.
No.

14:58.231 --> 14:59.721
How you said it made me sad.

15:00.024 --> 15:01.185
But will you do me a favor?

15:01.484 --> 15:03.521
Let them out
so I don't have to see him?

15:03.820 --> 15:06.938
<i>3 You like him
You really like him</i>

15:07.240 --> 15:09.652
What? That is so-- Me?

15:09.951 --> 15:11.692
Yeah. Just a little.
Care?

15:11.994 --> 15:14.952
Yeah.
About anything, ever!

15:15.248 --> 15:19.116
Especially something emotional
| don't care about at all?

15:19.419 --> 15:21.786
Does this look like me,
or look like somebody else?

15:22.088 --> 15:23.749
| think I can get away with it.

15:24.048 --> 15:25.004
Maybe an accent.

15:25.299 --> 15:26.960
Al right.

15:27.260 --> 15:29.001
Thank you very much, gentlemen,

15:29.303 --> 15:32.136
for choosing this particular
unlicensed limousine company

15:32.432 --> 15:33.888
for your Valentine's Day.

15:34.183 --> 15:35.264
Max?

15:36.561 --> 15:39.474
Hey. Grant.

15:39.772 --> 15:40.762
Happy Valentine's Day.

15:41.065 --> 15:43.853
Clark, this is Max.

15:44.152 --> 15:46.314
Great.
Another guy you know.

15:46.612 --> 15:47.773
| feel like
I'm swimming upstream

15:48.072 --> 15:49.654
against a steady current
of your ex-boyfriends.

15:49.949 --> 15:51.690
It's like I'm a gay salmon
fighting for my life

15:51.993 --> 15:52.983
in a river of bears.

15:54.287 --> 15:56.779
More of a cub, but...
[SCOFFS]

15:57.081 --> 15:59.038
Sorry you had to see
that mixed metaphor.

15:59.333 --> 16:02.416
Our relationship has been
really touch-and-go lately.

16:02.712 --> 16:05.374
He touches me,
and I go, stop touching me!

16:05.673 --> 16:06.663
[CHUCKLES]

16:06.966 --> 16:08.627
Sorry
you had to hear that, too.

16:08.926 --> 16:10.587
Well, I mean, he seems nice.

16:10.887 --> 16:12.173
He's taking you out
on Valentine's Day.

16:12.472 --> 16:13.928
Better than the last chump
you dated.

16:14.223 --> 16:15.930
Yeah.

16:16.225 --> 16:18.136
Hey, good to see you, Max.

16:18.436 --> 16:20.928
You too, man.
Happy Valentine's Day.

16:21.230 --> 16:22.436
[ALEX LAUGHS]

16:22.732 --> 16:24.598
Whoo, I knew it.

16:24.901 --> 16:26.938
You are the one that's supposed
to find love on Valentine's.

16:27.236 --> 16:28.522
Al, he's with another guy.

16:28.821 --> 16:30.482
Someone needs to find love,
or I'll freak.

16:30.781 --> 16:33.068
Guys. You know
how I was gonna dump Reed?

16:33.367 --> 16:34.823
Well, he just dumped me.

16:35.119 --> 16:38.908
| mean, he said I had this quirk
that he just couldn't stand.

16:39.207 --> 16:39.992
| hate how you abbreviate
everything.

16:41.042 --> 16:43.909
People love my abbreves.
They're cute.

16:44.212 --> 16:45.577
Penny, you asked my aunt
how she was feeling

16:45.880 --> 16:47.496
after her full hysterecto.

16:47.798 --> 16:50.586
| was trying
to keep the vibe light.

16:50.885 --> 16:52.125
Look. I wanted to wait
to break up with you

16:52.428 --> 16:53.509
because, you know,
the window.

16:53.804 --> 16:56.011
But I just can't.

16:56.307 --> 16:57.593
I'm sorry, Penny.

16:58.935 --> 17:02.724
Wait,
so are we actually done or...

17:03.022 --> 17:05.012
I'm confused.

17:05.316 --> 17:07.773
And then he said he hates
when I say "amazing."

17:08.069 --> 17:10.060
But I've barely said that at all
this season.

17:10.363 --> 17:11.569
You mean winter?
Yeah.

17:11.864 --> 17:12.819
It's more of a summer word.

17:13.115 --> 17:14.480
All right,
we all struck out, okay?

17:14.784 --> 17:16.319
But we are on our way
to pick up Dave and his girls.

17:16.618 --> 17:18.201
So let's rejoice in his love.

17:18.496 --> 17:19.861
[GROANS]
[GROANS]

17:23.876 --> 17:25.332
Well, I just blew a threesome.

17:25.627 --> 17:28.165
We talking two V's, one D?
Or two D's, one V?

17:28.464 --> 17:30.705
Two V's, Penny. Two V's.

17:31.008 --> 17:32.373
You and your breakup window.

17:32.677 --> 17:34.042
It's a thing. I'm sorry, Dave.

17:35.096 --> 17:37.212
| know this has been something
you've wanted for a long time.

17:37.515 --> 17:38.676
Your first e-mail was

17:38.975 --> 17:41.558
threesomechaser
@pulaskihillsmiddleschool.org.

17:41.852 --> 17:44.344
It sure was.
Thanks for understanding.

17:44.647 --> 17:47.765
All right, so it didn't work out
for me, you, Dave or Max.

17:48.067 --> 17:50.684
But I think Saint Valentine
is gonna come for Brad and Jane.

17:50.987 --> 17:52.398
Ooh!

17:52.697 --> 17:54.313
[BRAD GIGGLES]

17:56.534 --> 17:58.901
Oh, snap!

17:59.203 --> 18:02.116
We in a limo!

18:02.415 --> 18:04.656
[GROANING]

18:06.419 --> 18:08.751
Hey. Ross.

18:09.046 --> 18:11.788
Rachel. Phoebe.

18:12.091 --> 18:13.047
Fat Joey.

18:13.342 --> 18:15.174
[LAUGHING]
| love you guys.

18:17.597 --> 18:20.589
Brad went to the dentist today.
Got rip high.

18:20.891 --> 18:22.052
Poor guy.

18:22.351 --> 18:24.513
It's like
Weekend at Bernie Mac's

18:24.812 --> 18:27.099
Wait.
So your date was also a bust?

18:27.398 --> 18:29.435
Oh, God.

18:29.734 --> 18:31.600
| guess St. Valentine
isn't real.

18:31.902 --> 18:33.734
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

18:34.030 --> 18:35.361
Oh, it's Grant.

18:35.656 --> 18:37.363
"So much for Clark."

18:37.658 --> 18:39.990
"Another Valentine's Day ruined,
thanks to you."

18:40.286 --> 18:41.822
<O?

18:42.121 --> 18:44.078
Faith restored!

18:44.373 --> 18:46.205
St. Valentine
is gonna work his love magic

18:46.500 --> 18:48.867
for you and Grant.

18:49.170 --> 18:50.581
Guys, don't you see?

18:50.880 --> 18:52.666
Max and Grant are the ones
who are supposed to find love.

18:52.965 --> 18:53.921
Come on. Let's go get him.

18:54.216 --> 18:56.048
For love.
| can't just go get him.

18:56.344 --> 18:59.086
The reason he broke up with me
was I blew Valentine's Day.

18:59.388 --> 19:01.299
What am I gonna do?
Win him back with more nothing?

19:01.599 --> 19:04.637
| know a horsey!
Okay. I bet you do.

19:04.935 --> 19:07.518
Don't patronize me, Monica.

19:07.813 --> 19:09.099
That's it.

19:09.398 --> 19:10.934
We are gonna get you Grant.

19:11.233 --> 19:13.190
For love. Step on it!

19:13.486 --> 19:15.193
[ALEX WHOOPING]

19:18.991 --> 19:20.823
[240]

19:23.954 --> 19:25.865
Max. Hi.

19:26.165 --> 19:27.747
Uh...

19:29.210 --> 19:30.871
| just...
I'm so bad at apologies.

19:31.170 --> 19:32.331
| mean, so bad.

19:32.630 --> 19:34.041
Often another apology follows,

19:34.340 --> 19:35.671
which is then followed
by an apology text.

19:35.966 --> 19:37.582
And in one case,
a large cash settlement.

19:39.428 --> 19:43.137
| want to say I'm sorry, Grant,
about everything.

19:43.432 --> 19:46.515
And, um...
Happy Valentine's Day.

19:46.811 --> 19:48.893
[EXTREME'S "MORE THAN WORDS"
PLAYS]

19:51.649 --> 19:53.981
| thought you hated
Valentine's Day.

19:54.276 --> 19:55.482
| did.

19:55.778 --> 19:57.985
But I just thought
maybe with the right guy,

19:58.280 --> 20:00.146
it would be kind of okay,
you know.

20:00.449 --> 20:04.317
And since Dennis Farina
is straight,

20:04.620 --> 20:06.736
| thought, why don't you and |
hang out?

20:07.039 --> 20:09.497
| got you this.
It's a scarf. Whoops.

20:11.043 --> 20:13.205
Let's do it.

20:13.504 --> 20:15.461
[BRAD YELLING]

20:15.756 --> 20:16.211
We got the horsies.

20:17.258 --> 20:20.046
Right here!

20:23.222 --> 20:25.338
We should go,
this is a bit of a fire hazard.

20:25.641 --> 20:27.598
I'm just gonna blow these out.

20:27.893 --> 20:31.181
You guys, stop. We'll do that.
Max, you guys get in.

20:31.480 --> 20:32.561
Here. Fellas.

20:32.857 --> 20:33.813
Enjoy this,

20:34.108 --> 20:35.473
and our reservation at Tableau.

20:35.776 --> 20:37.266
It's gonna take forever
to get there,

20:37.570 --> 20:39.652
but at least it'll smell better
than Max's limo.

20:39.947 --> 20:41.312
Thanks.
[HORSE WHINNIES]

20:43.117 --> 20:45.154
| wouldn't actually touch
those blankets.

20:45.453 --> 20:46.784
| hear bums
have sex in these things

20:47.079 --> 20:48.945
when they're parked
in the park, you know.

20:54.503 --> 20:56.540
I'll shut up.

20:56.839 --> 20:57.795
Hyah!

21:02.178 --> 21:05.011
Oh! We did it.

21:05.306 --> 21:08.014
| want to give all of you guys
a big hug right now.

21:08.309 --> 21:09.799
Something the real Valentine
couldn't do

21:10.102 --> 21:11.934
after the Romans
ripped his arms and legs off.

21:12.229 --> 21:14.687
They went hard at that guy.
Was there anything left?

21:14.982 --> 21:16.438
Yeah, his heart.
Which they skewered

21:16.734 --> 21:18.475
and publically displayed
in the town's center.

21:18.778 --> 21:21.315
And that is why the heart
is the symbol of Valentine's.

21:21.614 --> 21:24.231
Aw...

21:24.533 --> 21:25.523
